title: Moldova voters choose pro-EU government over Moscow-leaning alliance – Europe live
summary: Moldovan President Maia Sandu has accused Russia of employing covert strategies to influence voter behavior in the country. She highlighted concerns over external interference in the democratic process. This accusation underscores escalating tensions between Moldova and Russia regarding electoral integrity.
